blurb: A common religion can bind people together linguistically, particularly if there is liturgical emphasis placed upon the original language of a sacred text. For example, the Jewish diasporas in US, Germany and Spain speak Hebrew, and Persian and Malay speakers learn Arabic.

A common religion can bind people together linguistically, particularly if there is liturgical emphasis placed upon the original language of a sacred text. For example, the Jewish diasporas in US, Germany and Spain speak Hebrew, and Persian and Malay speakers learn Arabic.
Cultural factors can contribute to a language’s spread. Many Chinese are learning Korean, perhaps both out of business needs and because of a growing taste for K-Pop.
